description:
&lt;p&gt;Applications are invited for an Associate Dean (General Practice) post as a result of promotion of the current incumbent.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The appointment is for 3 sessions each to support the training programme in the North Devon region. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The post holder will have a “portfolio” role based on the needs of HEESW GP School functions and a geographic “patch” role within the Postgraduate School of General Practice and will be responsible for GP programme management and stakeholder relationships across a number of locality programmes and Trusts across the patch.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The successful post holder will work as a member of the Primary Care team, contributing to strategic planning in the department, development and monitoring of standards in general practice education and training, and teaching on courses for GP educationalists.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful applicant will be based in North Devon and will provide patch responsibility and programme support. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Appointment will be made on the GP Educator scale GP03 .&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The successful applicant will have:&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;• A medical qualification, registered with the GMC on the specialist or GP register, with a licence to practise&lt;br /&gt;• Experience in medical education and training in general practice&lt;br /&gt;• An inspirational leadership style with the ability to lead within a team&lt;br /&gt;• Influencing and networking skills&lt;br /&gt;• An innovative and inclusive approach to delivering high quality multi-professional education&lt;br /&gt;• A sound understanding of quality management and medical education experience of working in a managed organisation in the NHS&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;For an informal discussion please contact Sarah Ansell : sarah.ansell@hee.nhs.uk &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameSarah AnsellJob titleHead of SchoolEmail addresssarah.ansell@hee.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
